git push --force-with-lease'

# Rename current branch
'git branch -M main'

# Remote Repositories
-View configured remotes
'git remote -v'

# Interactive Rebase (Advanced)
-Start interactive rebase
'git rebase -i <commit-hash>'
-Continue rebase
'git rebase --continue'
-Skip current commit
'git rebase --skip'
-Edit rebase todo list
'git rebase --edit-todo'

# Inspecting Commits
-Show a commit
'git show <commit-hash>'
-Show a specific file from a commit
'git show <commit-hash>:path/to/file'

# Restoring
-Unstage a file
'git restore --staged README.md or git reset HEAD file.txt'
-Discard changes to a file
'git restore README.md
git restore .'

# Cloning
-Clone a repository
'git clone <repository-url>'

# Changes Detection
-unstaged changes: It compares: Working Directory ↔ Staging Area
'git diff'
-staged files: It compares: Staging Area ↔ Last Commit
'git diff --staged
git diff --cached'
-Compare commits
'git diff commit1 commit2'
-Compare branches
'git diff main feature'
-Compare one file
'git diff README.md'
-See Changes Between Commits: Compare last commit with the current one
'git diff HEAD~1 HEAD'

# Reset to a Previous Commit
-Soft Reset (keeps changes in staging):
'git reset --soft HEAD~1'
-Mixed Reset (keeps changes in working directory):
'git reset HEAD~1'
-Hard Reset (discards all changes):
'git reset --hard HEAD~1'
--hard permanently deletes uncommitted work!

# .gitignore
"*.ext"   : detects all files with this ext and ignore them
"abc/"  : ignores the entire directory
"!abs.ext"  : ! is used for exception to *.ext
-Global .gitignore
-Set up a global ignore file for all repositories:
'git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore_global'
-Add it to .gitignore
'echo "passwords.txt" >> .gitignore'

# Removing Files from Git
-Remove File from Repository and Disk
'git rm file.txt
git commit -m "Remove file.txt"'

-Remove File from Repository but Keep on Disk
'git rm --cached file.txt
git commit -m "Stop tracking file.txt"'

# Moving/Renaming Files
-Git tracks file movements:
'git mv oldname.txt newname.txt
git commit -m "Rename oldname.txt to newname.txt"'

-This is equivalent to:
mv oldname.txt newname.txt
'git rm oldname.txt
git add newname.txt'

# View Current Branch
-The asterisk (*) shows your current branch:
'git branch'

-View All Branches (Including Remote)
'git branch -a'

# Creating and Switching Branches
-Create a New Branch
'git branch feature-navbar'

-Switch to a Branch
'git checkout feature-navbar'
-Or with the newer command:
'git switch feature-navbar'

-Create and Switch in One Command
'git checkout -b feature-navbar'
Or:
'git switch -c feature-navbar'

#Merging Branches
--Fast-Forward Merge
When there are no divergent commits, Git simply moves the pointer forward:
-On main branch
'git checkout main'
-Merge feature branch
'git merge feature-navbar'

--Three-Way Merge
When branches have diverged, Git creates a merge commit:
'git checkout main'
'git merge feature-login'

# Resolving Conflicts
"ours" = The branch you are currently on (the branch you are merging INTO)
"theirs" = The branch you are merging FROM (the incoming changes)
Keep current branch changes (ours):
'git checkout --ours index.html'
Keep incoming branch changes (theirs):
'git checkout --theirs index.html'
"Or you can manually change file content"

# Use a merge tool:
'git mergetool'

## Branch Management
# Delete a Branch
-After merging, you can delete the branch:

# Delete local branch
'git branch -d feature-navbar'
# Force delete (if not merged)
'git branch -D feature-navbar'

# List Remote Branches
'git branch -r'

# Delete Remote Branch
'git push origin --delete branch-name'

# Rename a Branch
- Rename current branch
'git branch -m new-name'
- Rename a different branch
'git branch -m old-name new-name'

# List Merged/Unmerged Branches
- Show merged branches
'git branch --merged'
- Show unmerged branches
'git branch --no-merged'

## Branching Strategies
# Feature Branch Workflow
1. Create feature branch
'git checkout -b feature-shopping-cart'
2. Work on feature
... make commits ...
3. Merge back to main
'git checkout main
git merge feature-shopping-cart'
4. Delete feature branch
'git branch -d feature-shopping-cart'

# Hotfix Workflow
1. Create hotfix from main
'git checkout main
git checkout -b hotfix-security'
2. Fix the issue
... make changes ...
'git commit -m "Fix security vulnerability"'
3. Merge to main
'git checkout main
git merge hotfix-security'
4. Also merge to develop if exists
'git checkout develop
git merge hotfix-security'

## Visualizing Branches
# See Branch Graph
'git log --graph --oneline --all'
# See Branch Divergence
'git log main..feature-branch'
- Shows commits in feature-branch that arenot in main.

## Fetch Changes
